    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant equipped with individual throttle bodies. This chassis is mated to a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul and professional reinforcement of the rear subframe mounting points to mitigate common floor-pan fatigue. The suspension geometry is maintained by refreshed control arm bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers, ensuring precise turn-in and mid-corner stability. While the Titan Silver finish shows minor road-wear consistent with its 'good' status, the powertrain remains in peak operating condition, delivering linear torque and a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. This is a purist-spec E46 optimized for tactile feedback and longitudinal performance.",
